summary: TL* THE CONTACT OWNS A 2017 JEEP WRANGLER. WHILE DRIVING APPROXIMATELY 25 MPH, ANOTHER VEHICLE DROVE THROUGH A STOP LIGHT AND COLLIDED WITH THE FRONT END AND FRONT PASSENGER SIDE OF THE CONTACT'S VEHICLE. THE AIR BAGS FAILED TO DEPLOY. THE DRIVER SUSTAINED INJURIES TO THE SHOULDERS, NECK, BACK, HIPS, AND LEGS THAT REQUIRED MEDICAL ATTENTION. A POLICE REPORT WAS FILED. THE VEHICLE WAS TOWED TO THE DEALER (JACKSONVILLE CHRYSLER, JEEP, DODGE AND RAM, 11101 NURSERYFIELDS DR., JACKSONVILLE, FL 32256, (904) 493-0000). THE VEHICLE HAD BEEN WAITING TO BE DIAGNOSED FOR OVER A MONTH. THE MANUFACTURER WAS MADE AWARE OF THE FAILURE AND THE CONTACT WAS ALSO AWAITING ON THEIR RESPONSE. THE VIN WAS NOT INCLUDED IN NHTSA CAMPAIGN NUMBER: 16V734000 (AIR BAGS). THE CONTACT MENTIONED THAT THE INSURANCE COMPANY REFUSED TO DEEM THE VEHICLE AS A TOTAL LOSS. THE VIN AND FAILURE MILEAGE WERE NOT AVAILABLE.
